commText: Ishan Kishan and Rohit are at the crease. Ishan Kishan is on strike. Vaibhav Arora will open the attack
Vaibhav Arora to Ishan Kishan, 1 run, full on leg-stump, flicked to square leg and there's a fumble, allows Ishan Kishan to get off strike
Vaibhav Arora to Rohit, wide, big inswinger but down leg, Rohit flicks and misses
Vaibhav Arora to Rohit, 1 run, this inswinger starts from outside off, Rohit gets a thick inside-edge on the defence, rolls past the leg-stump and they sneak a quick single
Vaibhav Arora to Ishan Kishan, 1 run, fullish outside off, steered nicely to deep backward point
Vaibhav Arora to Rohit, no run, full inswinger and heads to off-stump, Rohit covers it well with a big forward defence
Vaibhav Arora to Rohit, 1 run, full and snakes back in, Rohit with an ugly heave, thick inside-edge goes to deep backward square leg
Vaibhav Arora round the wicket.
Vaibhav Arora to Ishan Kishan, 1 run, full outside off, Ishan Kishan drives with an open face to deep backward point
Mitchell Starc, comes into the attack
Starc to Ishan Kishan, no run, full and angling into the pads, Ishan Kishan flicks and misses, rapped on the pads but sliding down
Starc to Ishan Kishan, FOUR, wide length delivery outside off, allows Ishan Kishan to free his arms, slapped over extra-cover and any width to Kishan and he will play
Starc to Ishan Kishan, SIX, this is a fine shot. A Fullish delivery on leg-stump, Ishan Kishan flicks it over square leg and it flies away 86m into the top tier. Starc can only shrug and walk back
Starc to Ishan Kishan, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!

Starc to Ishan Kishan, out Bowled!! Knocked him over. 142.3kph, full and on leg-stump, Ishan Kishan tries to heave and misses, the leg-stump is flattened. No big celebrations from Starc but that's a big wicket. Ishan Kishan b Starc 13(7) [4s-1 6s-1]
Naman Dhir, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Starc to Naman Dhir, no run, ooh! Went for the inswinging yorker on the stumps, is a low full-toss and pushed to mid-on

Starc to Naman Dhir, no run, big appeal for caught behind from Philip Salt but nothing from the others. Starc thinks it's pad. Full down leg, Naman Dhir flicks and misses, was it pad or bat? KKR don't review
Vaibhav Arora to Rohit, 1 run, full inswinger on off, flicked to deep mid-wicket
Vaibhav Arora to Naman Dhir, no run, short of length on off, Naman Dhir gets right behind the line to defend
Vaibhav Arora to Naman Dhir, no run, Naman Dhir tries to unsettle Vaibhav Arora as he gives the charge but misses the inswinger as he flicks, sliding down leg as it's rapped on the pads
Vaibhav Arora to Naman Dhir, FOUR, good pickup shot. Full and angling into off and middle, flicked between deep square leg and deep mid-wicket, right into the gap
Vaibhav Arora to Naman Dhir, no run, again Naman Dhir does not make contact, he comes down the track to flick, misses the full delivery down leg
Vaibhav Arora to Naman Dhir, FOUR, short outside off, Naman Dhir swivels and pulls over mid-wicket, no chance for Russell at deep mid-wicket
Starc to Rohit, 3 wides, full but down leg, Philip Salt dives to his left but half-stops, they take two more
Starc to Rohit, no run, full outside off, Rohit gets forward to push to cover
Starc to Rohit, SIX, what a shot. Full and angling away from Rohit who just gets forward and lofts on the rise over extra-cover, flies flat and all the way. I0$
Starc to Rohit, 1 run, very full on the boots, flicked to deep backward square leg
Starc to Naman Dhir, 2 runs, full outside off, driven to mid-off and Shreyas fires the throw, it ricochets off Starc I think and they take one more
Starc to Naman Dhir, no run, low full-toss on off, driven straight to the fielder at cover, hit hard and straight
Starc to Naman Dhir, 1 run, good length on middle, swung to deep square leg
Varun Chakaravarthy, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack
Chakaravarthy to Naman Dhir, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!

Chakaravarthy to Naman Dhir, out Bowled!! Chakaravarthy strikes first ball. Naman Dhir comes down the track to swing across the line, misses the delivery that angles in, hits the top of middle and leg. That sneaked through. Naman Dhir b Chakaravarthy 11(11) [4s-2]
Suryakumar Yadav, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Chakaravarthy to Suryakumar Yadav, 1 run, slower good length on middle, tucked to deep backward square leg
Chakaravarthy to Rohit, no run, tossed up fullish on middle, Rohit gently turns to mid-wicket
Chakaravarthy to Rohit, 1 run, tossed up full just outside off, driven wide of mid-off
Chakaravarthy to Suryakumar Yadav, no run, fullish outside off, driven wide of extra-cover who gets across and cuts it off on the slide
Chakaravarthy to Suryakumar Yadav, 1 run, the legbreak on a good length on middle, no turn, tucked to deep mid-wicket
Sunil Narine, right-arm off break, comes into the attack
Narine to Suryakumar Yadav, FOUR, back of a length outside off, Suryakumar Yadav punches and Russell at point dives to his right but the ball slips under the hand, should have stopped that
Narine to Suryakumar Yadav, 1 run, offbreak on a good length on the middle and leg line, tucked to deep square leg
Narine to Rohit, no run, tossed up offbreak on middle, flicked to square leg
Narine to Rohit, no run, tossed up on middle, Rohit goes for a big slogsweep, toe-ends it to short fine-leg
Narine to Rohit, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Narine to Rohit, out Caught by Manish Pandey!! Rohit goes and KKR are right back in this. A flat back of a length delivery on middle, Rohit goes on the back foot to pull, loops off the splice and Pandey at mid-wicket jogs back to take an easy catch. Never looked like dropping that. Rohit looks at his bat as he walks off. Rohit c Manish Pandey b Narine 11(12) [6s-1]
Rohit Sharma vs Sunil Narine in the IPL Runs: 141 Balls: 131 Dismissals: 8 Avg: 17.62 SR: 107.63

Bowler dismissing a batter most often in the IPL 8 - Sunil Narine - Rohit Sharma 7 - Sandeep Sharma - Virat Kohli 7 - Zaheer Khan - MS Dhoni 7 - Jasprit Bumrah - Rishabh Pant 7 - Bhuvneshwar Kumar - Ajinkya Rahane 7 - Mohit Sharma - Ambati Rayudu 7 - Amit Mishra - Rohit Sharma 7 - Ravichandran Ashwin - Robin Uthappa
Bowler dismissing a batter most often in T20s 10 - Dwayne Bravo - Kieron Pollard 10 - Sunil Narine - Rohit Sharma 9 - Sunil Narine - Shane Watson
Tilak Varma, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Narine to Tilak Varma, no run, Philip Salt goes "aigh" as Tilak Varma flicks and it's in the air for a while, finds mid-wicket
Powerplay summary -- Starc gets rid of Kishan for 13 (1.4) -- Starc goes for 13 in his 2nd over -- Chakaravarthy strikes first ball to castle Dhir (4.1) -- Narine gets rid of Rohit for 11 (5.5)
Chakaravarthy to Suryakumar Yadav, 1 run, 98.7kph length ball on off, leg-break, Surya hangs back and works it to long-on
Chakaravarthy to Tilak Varma, 1 run, low full toss outside off, driven to long-off

Chakaravarthy to Suryakumar Yadav, no run, Surya is early into the shot and it almost carries to Chakaravarthy! Flat length ball on middle, he looks to work it through the on-side but it straightens and stops on him, taking a soft leading edge. Chakaravarthy dives forward but can't get there
Chakaravarthy to Suryakumar Yadav, no run, flicked off the pads to short midwicket
Chakaravarthy to Suryakumar Yadav, no run, full outside off, pushed to short cover
Chakaravarthy to Suryakumar Yadav, 1 run, flat on middle, Surya hangs back and tucks it to long-on
Narine to Suryakumar Yadav, no run, length ball on middle, Surya hangs back and tucks it to backward square
Narine to Suryakumar Yadav, 2 runs, 96kph length ball on off, Surya bends across and sweeps nicely past short fine leg. Arora puts in a good effort in the deep to cut it off
Narine to Suryakumar Yadav, 1 run, flat length ball turning in on middle and leg, Surya gets forward and knocks it to long-on
Narine to Tilak Varma, no run, full outside off, Tilak goes hard on the drive and drags it off a thick inside edge onto pad
Narine to Tilak Varma, 1 run, flat length ball on off, 101kph, Tilak hangs back and punches it to long-off
Narine to Suryakumar Yadav, 1 run, back of a length on middle and leg, turning back in, and Surya punches it off the back foot to long-on
Chakaravarthy to Suryakumar Yadav, FOUR, dragged down short outside off, and punished! 108kph half-tracker, plenty of width for Surya to free his arms and he cuts nicely through backward point
Chakaravarthy to Suryakumar Yadav, 1 run, back of a length on leg, Surya tucks it through midwicket
Chakaravarthy round the wicket to Tilak
Chakaravarthy to Tilak Varma, 2 runs, full on middle and leg, turning back in, Tilak gets forward and flicks it through midwicket
Chakaravarthy to Tilak Varma, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Chakaravarthy to Tilak Varma, out Caught by Narine!! Tilak goes chasing after a wide one and edges it to short third! Chants of "KKR, KKR" at the Wankhede as Chakaravarthy gets his second. This is slightly slower through the air and very wide outside off. Would've been a wide had Tilak left it alone. But he goes chasing for the drive, isn't in control, and it loops off the edge to Narine who hangs onto a dolly. Tilak Varma c Narine b Chakaravarthy 4(6)
Timeout!
Nehal Wadhera, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Chakaravarthy to Nehal Wadhera, no run, length ball on middle, turning in, Wadhera looks to defend and gets it off the inside half to midwicket

Chakaravarthy to Nehal Wadhera, no run, 95.8kph back of a length on off, Wadhera looks to punch from the crease and gets a thick edge to short third. The fielder there is very fine. Would've probably run away for four if he was at a conventional position
Andre Russell, right-arm fast, comes into the attack
Russell to Suryakumar Yadav, 1 run, back of a length on middle, Surya tucks it through midwicket

Russell to Nehal Wadhera, FOUR, poor from Rinku in the deep! Back of a length outside off, Wadhera cuts hard but should've been cut off at deep point. However, Rinku overruns it while moving to his right
Russell to Nehal Wadhera, no run, slower bouncer outside off, left alone. Umpire calls it one for the over

Russell to Nehal Wadhera, no run, short ball over the right shoulder of Wadhera, he shuffles across to pull but misses. Umpire calls it wide, and KKR ask for the review. Third umpire says it's within the body, so it's not a wide down the leg-side, and it's not over head high either. Decision overturned
Russell to Nehal Wadhera, no run, close to the blockhole outside off, Wadhera squeezes it down the pitch
Russell to Nehal Wadhera, 1 run, back of a length outside off, pushed for a brisk run. Russell goes down after bowling this one, hopefully he is fine
Russell is on the floor and is being looked at by the physio. He slipped in followthrough in that previous delivery. Looks to be okay
Sunil Narine [2.0-0-10-1] is back into the attack
Narine to Nehal Wadhera, no run, length ball on off, defended forward
Narine to Nehal Wadhera, 1 run, on a length on leg-stump, turning away, pushed towards long-on and Sky doesn't want the second
Narine to Suryakumar Yadav, 1 run, Sky works this one towards deep mid-wicket
Narine to Nehal Wadhera, no run, full and quicker on off, pushed to covers
Narine to Nehal Wadhera, wide , full ball down leg, Nehal looks to sweep but misses
Narine to Nehal Wadhera, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!

Narine to Nehal Wadhera, out Bowled!! Another one bites the dust! Quicker and flatter outside off, Nehal Wadhera looks to slap it through covers perhaps but gets an inside edge which crashes into the stumps. Things going pear-shaped for MI. Nehal Wadhera b Narine 6(11) [4s-1]
Hardik Pandya, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Narine to Hardik Pandya, 1 run, full and drifting in on off, stroked down to long-off
Russell to Hardik Pandya, no run, back of a length outside off, punched to cover
Russell to Hardik Pandya, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Russell to Hardik Pandya, out Caught by Manish Pandey!! MI are collapsing spectacularly here. This is a length ball on the stumps, did it hold on Pandya? Who just jabs at it and it loops straight up, that's a strange shot across the line, played a bit too early, Russell for a moment wanted to go for the catch but sees Pandey at mid-wicket there and leaves it. A simple catch and KKR all over MI. Hardik Pandya c Manish Pandey b Russell 1(3)
Tim David, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Russell to Tim David, wide loopy bouncer and David lets it go. Called a wide and Russell is not happy, Shreyas reviews but the third ump deems it a wide for height, too high and KKR lose a review
Russell to Tim David, leg byes, 1 run, short of a length down leg, David flicks and misses, off the pad for a legbye, sliding down
Russell to Suryakumar Yadav, SIX, SKY picks the slower ball off-cutter on middle, swings it and clears the fine-leg fence, the fielder was just a spectator, MI needed that badly
Russell to Suryakumar Yadav, 2 runs, low full-toss on middle, flicked to deep square leg and a good sliding stop saves the four
Russell to Suryakumar Yadav, 1 run, another low full-toss on the stumps, driven to long-on
Narine to Suryakumar Yadav, 2 runs, tossed up full on the stumps, flicked wide of long-on and a great effort from Venky Iyer on the dive, saves four
Narine to Suryakumar Yadav, no run, good length and punched back
Narine to Suryakumar Yadav, 1 run, good length and turning back in, whipped aerially towards long-on
Narine to Tim David, no run, tossed up on the stumps, flicked to mid-wicket
Narine to Tim David, 1 run, short of a length and on the stumps, punched down to long-on
Narine to Suryakumar Yadav, FOUR, superb sweep. Tossed up full on off and middle, SKY gets low and sweeps wide of deep square, split the gap so well
Vaibhav Arora [2.0-0-15-0] is back into the attack
Vaibhav Arora to Tim David, 1 run, short ball outside off, David pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a single
Vaibhav Arora to Suryakumar Yadav, no run, back of a length ball outside off, SKY guides it straight to short fine

Vaibhav Arora to Suryakumar Yadav, FOUR, that's a trademark SKY shot! Shortish delivery outside off, SKY was waiting for it. He arches back and ramps it over short third to clear the fence. Brilliant batting

Vaibhav Arora to Suryakumar Yadav, no ball a low full-toss, SKY walks into the shot and drives it towards mid-off. The bat turned in his hand there. Arora has overstepped and a Free Hit is coming up...

Vaibhav Arora to Suryakumar Yadav, SIX, SKY takes full toll off the Free Hit! A low full-toss angling in, SKY crouches in his stance and goes inside out over covers to hit another maximum. He is so good and composed in these scenarios

Vaibhav Arora to Suryakumar Yadav, FOUR, SKY raises his fifty off 30 balls! He raises his bat and soaks in all the applause. He is playing a brilliant knock. Shortish delivery angling in, SKY stands tall and pulls it through square leg to find the fence

Vaibhav Arora to Suryakumar Yadav, FOUR, runs coming thick and fast now! Another short ball, predictive stuff. SKY pulls it with aplomb through backward square leg to find the fence again. 20 runs off the over

Chakaravarthy to Tim David, FOUR, edged but safe! Quick and flat outside off, David looks to cut it square of the wicket on the off-side but gets a thick edge past the keeper and the ball races to the third man fence
Chakaravarthy to Tim David, no run, 95.2kph full ball well outside off, David digs it out towards extra cover

Chakaravarthy to Tim David, 2 runs, on the shorter side outside off, David rocks back and cuts it through point. Starc in the deep moves to his left and dives to cut it off. Saves a couple for his side
Chakaravarthy to Tim David, 1 run, full ball drifting in on off, stroked down to long-off
Chakaravarthy to Suryakumar Yadav, 2 runs, flat length ball outside off, Surya gets forward and punches it through extra cover. He's back for two
Chakaravarthy to Suryakumar Yadav, no run, fuller than a length outside off, leg-break, Surya gets forward and knocks it to backward point

Overs summary (7-15) -- Narine & Chakaravarthy keep things tight -- Chakaravarthy strikes again as he gets rid of Tilak for 4 -- Narine knocks Wadhera over cheaply -- Russell gets rid of Pandya in quick succession -- Sky scores a flurry of boundaries in Arora's 3rd over to bring some momentum -- Sky raises a fifty off 30 balls -- 70 runs are scored in this phase of play
Chakaravarthy bowls out with 2/22. MI now need 51 off the last five overs
Andre Russell [2.0-0-16-1] is back into the attack
Russell to Tim David, 1 run, back of a length on off, David hangs back and tucks it through midwicket
Russell to Suryakumar Yadav, no run, 132.8kph yorker on middle, Surya digs it out to cover
Russell to Suryakumar Yadav, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Russell to Suryakumar Yadav, out Caught by Philip Salt!! Surya stands in disbelief while the KKR players come together in celebration. It takes a while for Surya to start walking back. He can't believe he's missed out on a full toss. It's usually bread and butter for him off his pads. But this time while looking to whip it away, he gets a thick leading edge and it goes a long way in the air. The keeper and fine leg converge, the keeper calls for it and takes it. Huge moment. Suryakumar Yadav c Philip Salt b Russell 56(35) [4s-6 6s-2]
Suryakumar Yadav vs Andre Russell in the IPL Runs: 49 Balls: 25 Dismissals: 3 Avg: 16.33 SR: 196 4s/6s: 4/4
Timeout!
Gerald Coetzee, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Russell to Gerald Coetzee, 1 run, slower ball on middle and leg, Coetzee works it gently through midwicket

Russell to Tim David, 2 runs, back of a length outside off, slower one, David shuffles across to work it through the on-side but it loops off a leading edge in front of cover. He scampers through to the other end as the throw comes in. Shreyas misses the stumps, and ends up giving an overthrow
Russell to Tim David, 1 run, full outside off, driven to long-off
Mitchell Starc [2.0-0-23-1] is back into the attack
Starc to Tim David, 1 run, back of a length on off, David stays in the crease and taps it through point
Starc to Gerald Coetzee, 1 run, full and wide, Coetzee reaches out and drives nicely through extra cover. There was a chance to take two but David wants strike
Starc to Tim David, no run, back of a length delivery just outside off, David looks to pull but is hit on the thigh. It wasn't short enough for that shot
Starc to Tim David, 1 run, back of a length outside off, again looks to pull and mistimes it to deep midwicket
Starc is jogging back to his mark while wiping the ball with the towel
Starc to Gerald Coetzee, no run, full outside off, drilled straight to extra cover
Starc to Gerald Coetzee, no run, slower short ball outside off, deceives Coetzee as he looks to cut and goes through to the keeper. Just three singles off the over

Russell to Tim David, no run, length ball just outside off, David shuffles across to clip it away but is hit on the pad. Russell goes up in appeal but gets no support. Was there an inside edge? Maybe just outside the line of off

Russell to Tim David, leg byes, 2 runs, another lone appeal from Russell for LBW. Slower length ball on middle and leg, David shuffles across looking to swipe it over short fine but misses. Is it too high? KKR have gone for the review. As suspected, ball-tracking says it's going over the top of leg stump
Russell to Tim David, 2 runs, back of a length delivery just outside off, David looks to pull and mistimes it to deep midwicket.
Russell to Tim David, 1 run, short of length outside off, slower one, David is deceived for lack of pace and mistimes the cut in the air. It falls safely in the point region

Russell to Gerald Coetzee, SIX, Coetzee clears the ropes! Welcome runs for MI with David struggling at the other end. Short of length at the body, Coetzee pulls well and hammers it over deep midwicket
Russell to Gerald Coetzee, no run, full and wide, Coetzee has a big swing but misses, a precious dot
Starc to Tim David, SIX, length ball slanted in on middle, David shuffles across, uses the angle from round the wicket to his advantage and swipes it over backward square
Starc to Tim David, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Starc to Tim David, out Caught by Shreyas Iyer!! David slumps on his haunches in agony. He's smashed a full toss straight to long-off. Glum faces in the MI dugout with the match now heavily in favour of KKR. The line is outside off with this full toss, and he seems to have hit it really well. Just doesn't get much elevation. Shreyas hangs onto the catch, takes off on a celebratory run and throws the ball away. Tim David c Shreyas Iyer b Starc 24(20) [4s-1 6s-1]
Piyush Chawla, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Starc to Chawla, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
Starc to Chawla, out Caught by Narine!! MI hopes are fading fast as Chawla goes first ball. Low full toss outside off, he looks to drive but toe-ends it to extra cover. Chawla c Narine b Starc 0(1)
Starc from round the wicket to Bumrah
Jasprit Bumrah, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Starc to Bumrah, 1 run, yorker on off, Bumrah squeezes it out in front of the keeper
Starc to Gerald Coetzee, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!

Starc to Gerald Coetzee, out Bowled!! The emotions are pouring out of Starc as he seals victory for KKR! Trademark yorker from round the wicket, Coetzee swings, misses, and the middle stump goes out of the ground. Gerald Coetzee b Starc 8(7) [6s-1]

23:16 Local Time, 17:46 GMT, 23:16 IST: Starc screams in delight while doing a double fist pump. He desperately needed that after a lackluster showing in this tournament so far. More importantly for KKR, they've staved off a late surge from the hosts to get the two points and consolidate second spot on the table. Seven wins in 10 games now, taking them ever closer to qualification. MI, on the other hand, are all but out. The pitch today was two paced and sticky, so the target of 170 wasn't a straightforward one. However, KKR had to overcome quite a bit of dew in the second innings and they did a fabulous job, especially their spinners. Chakaravarthy and Narine, both of them finished with identical figures of 2/22, including some big wickets in the first half of the chase which put KKR on top as MI were reduced to 71/6. Things got tight as Surya played a brilliant knock. But before he could tilt the balance, he perished to a full toss from Russell and MI didn't have much left in the tank after that.

Hardik Pandya | MI captain: I mean obviously in the batting inning, we couldn’t form partnerships and kept losing wickets, in T20s if you don’t form partnerships, it will cost you. Not much, there are a lot of questions but that will take some time to answer but for now, not much to say. As you mentioned, the bowlers did a fantastic job, the wicket got a little better after the first innings, the dew came on. We will go through the game and see what could we have done better. You keep fighting, that is what I tell to myself, never leave the battlefield, tough days come but good also come here, it’s challenging but challenges make you better.

Varun Chakaravarthy: Extremely good feeling for we have never won in Wankhede in 12 years and it's a great feeling to win here. We were still confident, it was a matter of one wicket. 170 was below-par and there was dew in the 2nd innings, but we controlled our emotions and stuck to our plans. [on if it spun in the 2nd innings] Not much in the 2nd innings as there was dew. We planned extensively for this match and it worked out. They did tell me that the ball is stopping but as I got to bowl, it was not stopping and it was going on well. Sunny is a legend, he has been bowling the same way from I don't know when. Glad to be bowling alongside him. This is a very special win for we were down and out in the first innings, the way Pandey and Venkatesh pulled off the game from their shoulders was great. It is sort of a comeback from the Punjab game when we conceded so many runs, so we said let's do it.
MI in run-chases in IPL 2024 Matches: 6 Won: 1 (vs RCB) Lost: 5
KKR vs MI at Wankhede Matches: 11 Wins: 2 Defeats: 9 KKR’s only previous win over MI at Wankhede came back in 2012, with Sunil Narine returning 4/15 from 3.1 overs in a 32-run win.
Pace vs spin in MI’s run-chase Spin: 4/44 in 8 overs (ER: 5.5) Pace: 6/98 in 10.5 overs (ER: 9.04) This was just the fourth instance of MI getting bowled out in 33 head-to-head contests against KKR.
Instances of both teams getting all-out in an IPL match DC vs RR, Nagpur, 2010 KKR vs RCB, Kolkata, 2017 MI vs SRH, Mumbai WS, 2018 MI vs KKR, Mumbai WS, 2024
4-fers for KKR vs MI 5/15 - Andre Russell, Chennai, 2021 4/15 - Sunil Narine, Mumbai WS, 2012 4/20 - Sunil Narine, Abu Dhabi, 2014 4/33 - Mitchell Starc, Mumbai WS, 2024
Stats by Roshan Gede

Shreyas, KKR captain: Just having a conversation with Starcy. Told him how important this game for us. If we lost this, would've had to win two out of four. Would take this anyday. Beautiful victory for us. Hope we could've cherished this one. But we have a match day after as well. Certainly, with this impact player rule, it has helped us in this game. Manish has been eyeing an opportunity from Day 1. Today he got it. We got to a commendable total. All I had to say to the boys was we can defend it with our bowling lineup. They were unreal to be honest (on the two spinners). Absolutely spot on in terms of execution with line and lengths. He's been eagerly waiting to go out and express himself in earlier games as well (on Venkatesh Iyer).

Venkatesh, POTM: As a professional cricketer, I have to be flexible in terms of situation. When I started hitting the ball well, two more wickets fell and I thought I have to play the anchor role. This is the fourth or fifth time Manish has padded up. This time he got to bat. Rather than sending Russell and Ramandeep higher, better to have Manish who can play the anchor role. Ball was holding and it was a two paced wicket. I try to be a smarter cricketer. Would've been easy for me to go after Piyush Chawla and the fast bowlers. Team needed me to be there till the end. I've been a huge fan of dada (Sourav Ganguly). Went to ask him about my stance and technical aspects. Was a fruitful conversation. It's coming through in my stance and other aspects in the nets.

KKR were reeling on 57/5 before impact sub Manish Pandey walked out and had a crucial partnership with Venkatesh Iyer who played brilliantly today. Their spinners then put on a show despite the dew, leading KKR to their first win at Wankhede in 12 years. Qualification shouldn't be far away now. That's all from us here. It's a goodbye from Sagar Chawla on behalf of Praveen Kumar and Abhinav Guha. See you tomorrow!
